dataset: Airbag and other influences on accident fatalities
dataset_description: US data, for 1997-2002, from police-reported car crashes in which there is a harmful event (people or property), and from which at least one vehicle was towed. Data are restricted to front-seat occupants, include only a subset of the variables recorded, and are restricted in other ways also.

dataset: Alcohol consumption in Australia and New Zealand
dataset_description: Data are annual apparent alcohol consumption in Australia and New Zealand, in liters of pure alcohol content per annum, separately for beer, wine, and spirits (including spirit-based products).

The Guyer data frame has 20 rows and 3 columns. The data are from an experiment in which four-person groups played a prisoner's dilemma game for 30 trails, each person making either a cooperative or competitive choice on each trial. Choices were made either anonymously or in public; groups were composed either of females or of males. The observations are 20 groups.
The houseprices data frame consists of the floor area, price, and the number of bedrooms for a sample of houses sold in Aranda in 1999. Aranda is a suburb of Canberra, Australia.
Cross-section data originating from the 1977-1978 Australian Health Survey.
Wages of employees of a US bank.

dataset: Benderly and Zwick Data - Inflation, Growth and Stock Returns
dataset_description: Time series data for Benderly and Zwick Data - Inflation, Growth and Stock Returns, from 1952 to 1982.
The dataset contains data on test performance, school characteristics and student demographic backgrounds for school districts in California.

The data are from an experiment that aimed to model the effects of the tinting of car windows on visual performance. The authors were mainly interested in effects on side window vision, and hence in visual recognition tasks that would be performed when looking through side windows.
Weekly observations on prices and other factors from 1880 to 1886, for a total of 326 weeks.
Time series of real national income in China per section (index with 1952 = 100).
Cross-section data on cigarette consumption for 46 US States, for the year 1992.

Cross-section data from the High School and Beyond survey conducted by the Department of Education in 1980, with a follow-up in 1986. The survey included students from approximately 1,100 high schools.
Cross-section data, at the firm level, on electric power generation.
The data are for psychiatric patients hospitalized for depression.
Cross-section data originating from the May 1985 Current Population Survey by the US Census Bureau (random sample drawn for Berndt 1991).
Subscriptions to economics journals at US libraries, for the year 2000.
Cross-section data on energy consumption for 20 European countries, for the year 1980.
Cross-section data on the credit history for a sample of applicants for a type of credit card.
Infidelity data, known as Fair's Affairs. Cross-section data from a survey conducted by Psychology Today in 1969.

Cross-section data for 675 14-year old children born between 1980 and 1988. The sample is taken from the German Socio-Economic Panel (GSOEP) for the years 1994 to 2002 to investigate the determinants of secondary school choice.
Growth regression data as provided by Durlauf & Johnson (1995).
Cross-section data on the Home Mortgage Disclosure Act (HMDA).

dataset: House Prices in the City of Windsor, Canada
dataset_description: Sales prices of houses sold in the city of Windsor, Canada, during July, August and September, 1987.

dataset: Impact of Beauty on Instructor's Teaching Ratings
dataset_description: Data on course evaluations, course characteristics, and professor characteristics for 463 courses for the academic years 2000–2002 at the University of Texas at Austin.
Cross-section data originating from the 1976 Panel Study of Income Dynamics (PSID), based on data for the previous year, 1975.
US time series data on prices and cost shares in manufacturing

Cross-section data originating from the 1986 Medicaid Consumer Survey. The data comprise two groups of Medicaid eligibles at two sites in California (Santa Barbara and Ventura counties): a group enrolled in a managed care demonstration program and a fee-for-service comparison group of non-enrollees.
Cross-section data originating from the Medical Expenditure Panel Survey survey conducted in 1996.
The headInjury data frame has 3121 rows and 11 columns. The data were simulated to match roughly the clinical characteristics of a sample of individuals who suffered minor head injuries.
Panel data originating from 6 US states over the period from 1967 to 1989.

dataset: Number of Equations and Citations for Evolutionary Biology Publications
dataset_description: Analysis of citations of evolutionary biology papers published in 1998 in the top three journals (as judged by their 5-year impact factors in the Thomson Reuters Journal Citation Reports 2010).

dataset: Properties of a Fast-Moving Consumer Good
dataset_description: Time series of distribution, market share and price of a fast-moving consumer good.

The 2008-09 nine-month academic salary for Assistant Professors, Associate Professors and Professors in a college in the U.S. The data were collected as part of the on-going effort of the college's administration to monitor salary differences between male and female faculty members.

dataset: Structure of Demand for Medical Care
dataset_description: Structure of Demand for Medical Care
The cane data frame has 180 rows and 5 columns. The data frame represents a randomized block design with 45 varieties of sugar-cane and 4 blocks.
Television rights for Olympic Games for US networks (in millions USD).
Statewide data on transportation equipment manufacturing for 25 US states.
Data on travel mode choice for travel between Sydney and Melbourne, Australia.
The Anscombe data frame has 51 rows and 4 columns. The observations are the U. S. states plus Washington, D. C. in 1970.
US traffic fatalities panel data for the “lower 48” US states (i.e., excluding Alaska and Hawaii), annually for 1982 through 1988.
WHO Monica Data
